g.text: The feet are among the parts of the body that suffer the most from work accidents. According to the INSS study, over 39,000 accidents were recorded in the foot region, except for the toes. This places this region of the body as the 2nd that suffers most work accidents.

Made especially for the skin care of babies, some baby wipeshave a soft and delicate touch as they have over 90% water in their composition. In addition, they have no fragrance, so as not to cause strangeness in the little ones.Ideal for use as early as the baby's first months of life.

As the child draws, she develops various skills. Controlling a pencil or crayon in a tweezing movement develops motor coordination. This happens from the age of 3, when the child moves from doodling to more meaningful drawing.
